title: Virgin Australia flight makes emergency landing at air force base - 9news.com.au
text:
Virgin Australia flight makes emergency landing at air force base By James Gorman 
A Virgin flight from Port Macquarie to Sydney has been forced to land at a RAAF base in Newcastle due to smoke in the cabin. 
Fire and Rescue NSW Fire told 9News they were called to the air force base at 3:06pm after flight VA1188 made an emergency landing. 
Air force fire services also attended the scene. 
Virgin Australia confirmed all passengers were evacuated off the plane safely. 
Early reports indicate the smoke originated from the cockpit.
